<subSubSection id="A6D23D89FFDC0F2EFF00FEF5FE3A9C77" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EE776E02FFDC0F2EFF00FEF5FDCE982B" blockId="4.[151,1437,259,574]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDC0F2EFF00FEF5FDAF9B0B" bold="true" box="[151,574,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Distribution and additional records</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="29C81581FFDC0F2EFDDBFEF2FD4D9B0B" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1877" box="[588,732,259,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDC0F2EFDDBFEF2FD4D9B0B" box="[588,732,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Brycon ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDC0F2EFC0BFEF5FBB99B0B" author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[924,1064,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Lima (2017)</bibRefCitation>
as occurring from the rio Itaúnas in northern 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDC0F2EFE8DFED1FE699B57" box="[282,504,295,321]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Espírito Santo State</collectingRegion>
northward to the rio dos Frades basin in southern 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDC0F2EFBBCFED1FB389B54" box="[1067,1193,295,322]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Bahia state</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="96DF2E92FFDC0F2EFB23FED1FB6D9B57" box="[1204,1276,295,321]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. However, the species was also recorded from the rio São Mateus in 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDC0F2EFD6DFEBDFC0B9B73" box="[762,922,331,357]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
(immediately southward to rio Itaúnas basin) by 
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDC0F2EFF2EFE99FD3C9B9F" author="Sarmento-Soares, L. M. &amp; Martins-Pinheiro, R. F." box="[185,685,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref11754" refString="Sarmento-Soares, L. M. &amp; Martins-Pinheiro, R. F. (2012) A fauna de peixes nas bacias do norte do Espirito Santo, Brasil. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas, 12 (1), 1 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 118" type="journal article" year="2012">Sarmento-Soares &amp; Martins-Pinheiro (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDC0F2EFD2FFE99FC069B9F" author="Plesley, P. A. S. &amp; Duboc, L. F. &amp; Ingenito, L. F. S." box="[696,919,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="229 - 241" refId="ref11467" refString="Plesley, P. A. S., Duboc, L. F. &amp; Ingenito, L. F. S. (2014) Levantamento ictiofaunistico em dois pontos da sub-bacia do rio Preto do Sul, Sao Mateus, Espirito Santo, frente a aspectos ambientais. In: Sarmento-Soares, L. M., Lirio, E. and Martins- Pinheiro, R. F. (Eds.), Anais do III Simposio Sobre a Biodiversidade da Mata Atlantica (SIMBIOMA): areas protegidas e biodiversidade. Santa Tereza: Sociedade dos Amigos do Museu de Biologia Mello Leitao. Sociedade dos Amigos do Museu de Biologia Mello Leitao, Santa Teresa, pp. 229 - 241." type="book chapter" year="2014">
Plesley 
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDC0F2EFC98FE86FCD79B9F" box="[783,838,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
and Mazzini 
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDC0F2EFBB9FE86FBF49B9F" box="[1070,1125,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">et al.</emphasis>
(2014), a fact unfortunately omitted by 
<bibRefCitation id="8A5913F3FFDC0F2EFE8AFE65FE219BBB" author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[285,432,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Lima (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. In addition, recent expeditions made by LFSI and collaborators to the river drainages from northern 
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDC0F2EFEACFE41FE4A9BC7" box="[315,475,439,465]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
(rio Itaúnas, rio São Mateus, and rio Barra Seca basins), and by LNR to the upper rio Barra Seca revealed that 
<taxonomicName id="29C81581FFDC0F2EFE2FFE2AFD839BE3" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1877" box="[440,530,475,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis id="DCBCB210FFDC0F2EFE2FFE2AFD839BE3" box="[440,530,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">B. ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the region (
<figureCitation id="76F37287FFDC0F2EFC27FE2DFB9F9BE3" box="[944,1038,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1104,1128]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1081]" captionTargetId="figure-193@4.[151,1436,597,1081]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Brycon ferox, CZNC 1648, 134,12 mm SL: Brazil, Espírito Santo, rio São Mateus basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5733630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5733630/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">figure 3</figureCitation>
). With the new information herein provided, the distribution of the species extends southward to the rio Barra Seca (
<collectingRegion id="2C0CA0E0FFDC0F2EFBB0FE09FB5C980F" box="[1063,1229,511,537]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
), which is situated immediately north of the rio Doce basin.
</paragraph>
